James de Villiers, News24 (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A 46-year-old man is in critical condition after he fell 2m from a pier at the Durban Harbour on Friday, paramedics said. Paramedics found him at the scene trapped between concrete blocks in the water, Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha said in a statement.&nbsp;Police and firefighters managed to pull the man back onto the pier.&nbsp;He was taken to a nearby hospital for further care.&nbsp;Botha told News24 that the part of the pier from where the man fell is a well-known fishing spot and he could possibly have been fishing when he fell into the water.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.